reviews.review: I thought it was ok. I stood in line for Star Wars IV on 1977 and was in awe. Can't say that about this one. I'm glad they respected Luke Skywalker at the end of this. I was pretty upset at the last one. Mandalorian is more my thing. now.
Acting liked. Story liked. Not anything to dislike.
Was a great movie with great plot and twists!
Good sequel. JJ Abrams did well with what he was given. Hard to come to an end of an era and start a new one. A new direction with good vision and writing can be very successful.
Headache-inducing roller-coaster ride with nothing new to add to a creatively bankrupt franchise and no emotional backbone

Finally!  Closure after 42 years!  This movie was entertaining from start to finish.  I'm sad to say goodbye to the Skywalker saga but excited to see what's next.  The yellow light saber at the close was subtly perfect!

Just awful from start to finish. Didn't even have any nice cinematography and wasted what cool sets it had by not properly establishing it. What a waste to the rest of the trilogy. 

GG on living up to your brand JJ.

Too little too late. A good attempt to try and redeem a failed sequel trilogy, but the damage has already been done. Therefore, the movie is rushed, convoluted, and spends an awkward amount of time trying to right the new series wrongs. It's an appreciated attempt but doesn't completely succeed.

Director JJ Abrams gives us an unimaginative and predictable finish to the Star Wars saga by evoking nostoglia and a campy ex machina ending. Unfortunately, the damage from former director Last Jedi combined with the New Hope rewrite that was Abram's first film in the series proves too great for us to actually care much for most of the new characters introduced in this trilogy. As far as endings to a long saga go, I can say it wasn't as disappointing as Game of Thrones. However, they did sideline Rose, the second worst character of the Star Wars franchise (looking at you Jar Jar), so I give it a merciful 2 stars.
I thought daisy Ridley and Kylo ren really carries the show. Their intensity was fearsome. FX were Normal Star Wars - good. But the story of those two was unexpected yet satisfying.
